g.text: Employment to population ratio and unemployment rate and in Greater Melbourne and the rest of Victoria

text.style: font-size: 14.00px; font-weight: bold; fill: #004676; font-family: sans;

g.text: The unemployment rate in Greater Melbourne was 6.9 per cent while the rate in the rest of Victoria was 4.7 per cent in March 2021
Source: ABS Labour Force, Detailed (monthly). Note: most recent data is for March 2021. Data not seasonally adjusted. Smoothed using a 3 month rolling average.
